OraItaliana; // Indice 11 corrisponde alla colonna 12 } // Aggiungi la riga creata all'array di dati XML xmlRowData.push({data: xmlRow, sheetName: destinationSheetName}); }); } // Inserisci tutte le righe in xmlRowData nei rispettivi fogli di destinazione xmlRowData.forEach(rowData => { const destinationSheet = spreadsheet.getSheetByName(rowData.sheetName); if (destinationSheet) { destinationSheet.appendRow(rowData.data); // Inserisci la riga nel foglio di destinazione } }); } catch (e) { Logger.log(\\"Errore nell'elaborazione del file XML: \\" + e); } } } function estraiValoreTag(element, tag) { // La restante logica rimane invariata fino a \\"return nonEmptyResults.join('n');\\" // Modifica il return finale: return nonEmptyResults; // Restituisci l'array di valori non vuoti } function getDataEOraItaliana() { // Questa funzione rimane invariata ... } function generaUnixTimestampConFusoOrarioItaliano() { // Questa funzione rimane invariata ... } \`\`\` Questo codice ora fornirÃ  un array di dati, dove ogni valore estratto da un tag XML viene trattato come una riga separata, garantendo che non ci sarÃ  alcun dato multilinea inserito in un'unica cella del foglio di calcolo. Ricorda di modificare \`\\"YOUR_FOLDER_ID_HERE\\"\` con l'ID reale della tua cartella. Inoltre, assicurati che la lunghezza della tua riga (\`xmlRow\`) abbia abbastanza colonne per includere \`idDoc\` e \`dataEOraItaliana\`. Se il numero di colonne non Ã¨ corretto, aggiusta gli indici appropriati nella sezione che aggiunge \`idDoc\` e \`dataEOraItaliana\` per farli corrispondere alla struttura della tua tabella. Sottolineo l'importanza di testare questo script in un ambiente di sviluppo per verificarne l'effettiva funzionalitÃ  prima di utilizzarlo in produzione."},{"prompt":"Design a new custom in-depth and intense lore narrative, within LANCER (made by Massif Press), that ends in a disaster. This disaster is a cliff-hanger.","completion":"Title: **Cipher's Maelstrom** Prologue: Long after the dissolution of Union, humanity's golden era of interstellar expansion, a contingent of far-reaching colonies and worlds has stumbled upon an ancient relic of incalculable significance. Known as the Cipher Conduit, this device is believed to be a key left behind by the ineffable Precursors - a cryptic race rumored to have seeded the universe with life and technology before vanishing into the cosmos. The discovery of such an artifact has set the major factions of the galaxy ablaze with greed, curiosity, and fear. Chapter 1: **The Awakening of the Cipher** A team of LANCERs, elite mech pilots hailing from the independent world of Pyrrhic Bastion, is tasked with the protection of the Cipher Conduit after its unearthing on the fringe planet of Veil-7. These Lancers, under the banner of researcher Dr. Elion Voss, activate the Conduit, whose omnilingual interface resonates with the mind of codename Oracle, the team's polyglot and communications expert. Linking mind to machine, the Cipher blossoms into life, projecting a star map that spans the known and unknown universe. Chapter 2: **The Harbingers' Plight** Triumphant in their discovery, silence soon befalls the team as the star map flickers with rapidly dimming stars, ancient worlds snuffed out in an echoing cascade. An interstellar historian within Voss' circle, codename Archivist, conjures a chilling interpretation: the Cipher Conduit is retracing the steps of some galactic cataclysm, a sweeping erase that could soon reach their current realm. Chapter 3: **Echoes of Dominion** The Cipher's star map draws the unwanted attention of the Drowned Fleet, a rogue armada led by the fearsome admiral known as Leviathan, whose behemothic mech, Tsunami, crushes resistance as the fleet looms over Veil-7. Intent on weaponizing the Cipher's secrets and tracing the path of the precursor cataclysm to harness its power, the Fleet engages the planet's defenses. Pyrrhic Bastion's LANCERs are drawn into the conflict, Oracle's mind agonizingly stretched between the Cipher's cryptic cries and the battlefield's chaotic hymn. Chapter 4: **The Bloodied Light** The war on Veil-7 reaches a critical zenith as the Bastion's LANCER team, through sweat and blood, repels the Drowned Fleetâ€™s onslaught, driving a spear into the heart of Tsunami, casting Leviathan into the abyss of space. Yet, in the heat of the final battle, the Cipher sings a new, somber tune, a dirge that casts the Lancers and their cohorts into stunned silence. Chapter 5: **The Waking Storm** The Cipher, now amplified by the Climactic Clash, sends a surging pulse of energy that tears reality asunder, unveiling a colossal rift above Veil-7. A monstrous entity from the breach, tentatively named The Maelstrom, swirls into being. It is neither mech nor flesh, defying understanding, enveloping stars in its swirling tendrils. Chapter 6: **Cipher's Requiem** As Dr. Voss and his team, alongside the recovering forces of Veil-7, confront the emerging Maelstrom, they realize the immense power of the Cipher has awoken something far beyond their comprehension. The Maelstrom's presence gnaws at reality, threatening to extend its nightmarish reach across the galaxy. Epilogue: **The Descent Into Darkness** The planet Veil-7 buckles under the Maelstrom's weight; the skies rend apart with eldritch fury as stars twist and contort into obsidian voids. Oracle, linked inextricably to the Cipher, screams out a cryptic message: \\"The architects flee their creation, for the darkness woven into the canvas of the cosmos has found the breach. The keys turn, the locks shatter, the end begins anew.\\" The Lancer team stands at a precipice, the fate of the universe in the balance, as Veil-7 succumbs to catastrophe. The Cipher's song, once promising the fruits of ancient wisdom, now serenades the galaxy with the promise of its end. The Cipher Conduit dims, The Maelstrom pulses, and the universe holds its breath. To be continued..."},{"prompt":"Design a new custom in-depth and intense lore narrative, within LANCER (made by Massif Press), that ends in a disaster. This disaster is a cliff-hanger. Try not to include any single persons.","completion":"Title: **The Tears of Polyphemos** Backdrop: In a distant sector of space, a reclusive faction of Horizon Corporation scientists stationed on the research world of Aenigma have tirelessly decoded the genomic blueprints of ancient titan-class bioengineered organisms, remnants of a long-dead precursor civilization known as the Myrmidons. Among the squabbling successor states which arose in the wake of Union's decline, this discovery promises to shift the balance of power and provoke the fires of war over control of pre-collapse technologies. Chapter 1: **Eureka at Aenigma** The Horizon Corporation's scientists, based on Aenigma, utilized their LANCER contracted outfits to secure and study the unique biosphere riddled with precursor DNA. Encased within colossal dormant spores found buried on the planet surface, the bio-codes represent potential living weapons of incomparable strength, dubbed \\"The Myrmidonic Progeny,\\" yet their true nature remained shrouded in enigma. Chapter 2: **Conclave of Greed** The resurgence of these ancient blueprints turned Aenigma into a focal point for the galaxyâ€™s powers, with spies and mercenaries dispatched to secure any sliver of the biomolecular secrets. Before long, a clandestine Conclave of Warlords, Sovereign Corporations, and Free Mercenary States has called for a summit on the mining moon of Goliath-9 orbiting Aenigma, their eyes set upon the proverbial genetic treasure trove. Chapter 3: **The Gears of Janus** The summit on Goliath-9, projected as a peace-keeping effort, becomes the epicenter of clandestine sabotage and political machinations. As the conclave bitterly argues over proprietary claims, a faction among them secretly engineers a coup, aiming to hijack Aenigma's control facilities and unleash the Myrmidonic Progeny as their unbridled instrument of conquest. Chapter 4: **Awakening of Giants** An insidious plot unfolds as the traitorous faction triggers the ancient terraforming engines hidden deep within Aenigma's crust. These colossal machines, once purposed for sculpting entire worlds in the Myrmidonâ€™s image, now pulse with lifeâ€”initiating a cataclysmic reawakening of the dormant spores. A gargantuan ecosystem bursts forth, a testament to the Myrmidonâ€™s mastery of bioarchitecture. Chapter 5: **The Loom of Threads Undone** The tentative peace shatters as bio-titans, the Myrmidonic Progeny, rise from the soil and sea of Aenigma in a terrifying display of engineered evolution. Each colossal being a convergence of flora, fauna, and unfathomable technology, they begin a seemingly purposeful march across the star system. Goliath-9 and other nearby installations are caught in the path of these migrating behemoths, facing impending destruction. Chapter 6: **The Endling's Dirge** United in panic and desperation, the factional armadas amass, turning their weapons towards Aenigma in a futile attempt to quell the awakening. Embroiled in chaotic skirmishes with the proliferating bio-titans, the fleets lay siege to the planet. The world trembles as each goliathâ€™s song joins an ancient chorusâ€”a haunting melody growing ever louder, the call of a species denied death by their creators, seeking an end to their eons-long purgatory. Epilogue: **The Schism Unleashed** As the factions reel from the world-spanning resonance of the Endlingâ€™s Dirge, spatial anomalies begin to tear at the very fabric of reality. From these rifts, an indescribable force surges forthâ€”energies and entities predating the cosmos, drawn to the siren call of the bio-titans. The void gapes wide, the world of Aenigma fractures under the strain, and yet a greater disaster looms. The horizon bleeds with the light of birthing stars and collapsing relativity, the echoes of an ancient demise now mirrored in the eyes of a galactic civilization teetering on the brink of its own oblivion. To be continued..."},{"prompt":"Design a new custom in-depth and intense lore narrative, within LANCER (made by Massif Press), that ends in a disaster. This disaster is a cliff-hanger and faster-than-light is impossible.","completion":"Title: **The Paradox of Seraphim's Reach** Backdrop: In the wake of Unionâ€™s fragmentation, humanity has spread across the cosmos at sub-light speeds, using time-dilating relativistic travel to colonize distant worlds. Without faster-than-light capabilities, vast sleeper ships and time-dilated fleets navigate the gulfs between stars, carrying colonists who will never see the homes or eras from which they departed. One such world, designated Seraphimâ€™s Reach, is at the edge of known space, a crown jewel of a planet teeming with exotic, but hostile life, orbiting a binary star system. Here, an isolated colony thrives, developing a society guided by the pre-collapse ambition of Union to forge humanityâ€™s place among the stars. Chapter 1: **Anomaly at the Edge** Within Seraphim's Reach, engineers detect an inexplicable anomaly in local space-timeâ€”a fluctuation that defies their understanding of physics. LANCER units, deployed to investigate, discover a vast subterranean structure, the Nexus Vault, its architecture betraying no known human or xeno design and radiating with the temporal anomaly's energy. Chapter 2: **Echoes from the Eventide** As the Nexus Vault is activated unintentionally during the LANCERsâ€™ exploration, a dormant system comes aliveâ€”casting out spectral images of civilizations and events spanning across parallel timelines. These ghostly echoes reveal potential destinies and untapped technologies hidden within the currents of time, testaments to myriad human achievements and disasters rigorously documented within the Nexus' archives. Chapter 3: **The Weave of Epochs** The data extracted from the Nexus reveals a staggering truth: Seraphim's Reach has become the unwilling synchrony point for a convergence of timelines. The planet is set as nexus in a tapestry of epochs, a point of unity for infinite dimensions. The possibility for untold knowledge and power incites a fervent drive among the colonyâ€™s factions to master the Nexus' secrets, leading to inevitable conflict. Chapter 4: **The Gathering Tempest** The time-stressed conflict spirals out of control as LANCER mechs clash in brutal skirmishes for dominion over the Nexus Vault. Outside the conflict, scholars and scientists desperately attempt to stabilize the anomaly, fearing that the disturbance might precipitate a catastrophic cascade through the fabric of space-time, unraveling the cosmos itself. Chapter 5: **The Seraphim's Gambit** In a final attempt to seize the Nexus, one faction deploys an ancient, experimental device rumored to manipulate time. The gambit backfires catastrophically. The device resonates with the Nexus anomaly, amplifying its reach exponentially. Synchronized timelines begin to bleed into each other, creating paradoxes and anachronisms. Chapter 6: **Rifts in the Firmament** Reality tears as synchronicity grinds against the natural flow of time. Entire sections of Seraphim's Reach are displaced, exchanged with their counterparts from other timelinesâ€”forests become deserts, oceans turn into mountains, and alien creatures appear amidst the chaos. LANCER units scramble to respond, now fighting to preserve not just their dominion but their very existence. Epilogue: **Collapse Into The Inevitable** The planet quakes as the very foundations of time threaten to collapse. The Nexus Vault pulses with a blinding light, its structure crumbling as the anomaly exceeds critical thresholds. Reality itself is stretched thin, the fabric of existence on the brink of being torn asunder. From the heart of the dying Nexus, a rift engulfs the world. A silence falls, sudden and deep, as all waits on the precipice of the unfathomable. What lies beyond is an abyss of impossibilities, a disaster from which there may be no return. To be continued..."},{"prompt":"Design a new custom in-depth and intense lore narrative, within LANCER (made by Massif Press), that ends in a disaster. This disaster is a cliff-hanger and ends with faster-than-light speed becoming impossible.","completion":"Title: **Horizon's Eclipse** Backdrop: In the era following the fall of Union, humanityâ€™s colonization and expansion efforts have leveraged emergent faster-than-light (FTL) technology, a transcendent triumph over the vast distances of the cosmos. A network of FTL lanes, known as the Veins of Helios, forms the backbone of interstellar travel and trade, interconnecting humanity's sprawling settlements and planets. Amidst the fragile peace, the Midas Collective, a league of technocrats and scientists, seeks to enhance the Veins of Helios through the Helios Expansion Project, aiming to stitch together even more distant stars and fortify the lifelines of human space. Chapter 1: **The Helios Expansion Project** The Midas Collective assembles a flotilla of LANCER pilots, engineers, and astrophysicists for an ambitious missionâ€”extend the Veins of Helios into the uncharted Tartarus Expanse. Their plan is to deploy a series of deep-space FTL beacons to sustain a stable FTL corridor that will unite far-reaching colonies and bring prosperity to the edges of known space. Chapter 2: **Anomaly in Tartarus** The LANCER flotilla reaches Tartarus Expanse, but soon faces unforeseen interferenceâ€”the FTL beacons suffer from erratic fluctuations, and ships find themselves disoriented upon exit. Probes reveal a mysterious dark-matter construct deep within Tartarus, affecting local spacetime and distorting FTL travel. The findings send ripples of concern through the Collective, raising the question of whether the Expanse can, or should, be tamed. Chapter 3: **The Tartarus Construct** Despite concerns, the mission proceeds. An elite LANCER unit is deployed to secure and investigate the construct. As they draw near, they find the structure is not just an aberration of matter but an intricate network that manipulates spacetime in its vicinityâ€”an ancient relic potentially predating human spaceflight. Chapter 4: **Harbinger's Arrival** The exploration of the dark-matter construct leads to a catastrophic discoveryâ€”exact resonance with the FTL beacons imperils the stability of the Veins of Helios. The unfathomable energies involved threaten to unspool the fabric of FTL space. Disruptions cascade along the network, and LANCER units across the galaxy report malfunctions and navigational hazards increasing in severity. Chapter 5: **The Unraveling Pathways** As the Collective issues an immediate halt to the Helios Expansion Project, it's too late. The continuum of FTL space begins to unravel, the dark-matter harmonics from the Tartarus Construct distorting the Veins of Helios beyond repair. Ships are stranded, communications break down, and colonies once hops away now face isolation that could span lifetimes. Chapter 6: **Eclipse of Helios** Galactic civilization teeters on the brink of regression as the Veins of Helios deteriorate. LANCER pilots and their allies make a last-ditch effort to mitigate the damage, but the dark-matter construct activates, signaling the end of an era. A pulse of unseen energy expands from Tartarus, severing the delicate threads of FTL travel across the galaxy in an instant. Epilogue: **The Infinite Drift** The cascade reaches a climax as FTL travel is rendered impossible. The lights of the beacons die out one by one, leaving the galaxy in stunned silence. The once-united human settlements are left to face their new realities, separated by aeons of void. As the flotilla drifts in the darkness of Tartarus, powerless to return, theyâ€”and all of humanityâ€”stand on an unprecedented precipice: In a galaxy now infinite in its distance, what will become of the human endeavor? To be continued..."},{"prompt":"Generate an enjoyable, intense, and engaging plot for a campaign for the LANCER TTRPG, made for beginner LANCER players. The campaign must be able to introduce the players to the mechanics of the TTRPG.","completion":"Campaign Title: **Titanfall Rhapsody** Campaign Overview: In \\"Titanfall Rhapsody,\\" a group of rookie LANCER pilots are conscripted into the United Earth Defense Force (UEDF) to protect humanityâ€™s frontiers against a menagerie of threats: rogue AI, alien beasts, insurrectionists, and the mysteries of the cosmos itself. This campaign is designed to slowly introduce the basic mechanics of combat, exploration, and role-playing in the LANCER TTRPG, while providing an engaging story that unfolds over the course of five distinct but interconnected missions. **Session 0: Initiation and Calibration** Players create their characters, selecting licenses and building their mechs with guidance from the game master (GM). The session includes a mini tutorial scenario that teaches combat basics and role-playing elements. Mission Setting: Located on the fringe planet of Promethea, the UEDF managerial hub, Fort Halcyon, is a bustling military base teeming with LANCER hopefuls, engineers, and base personnel. **Mission 1: Shakedown Cruise** *Objective*: Conduct a routine patrol around the Fort Halcyon perimeter and calibrate your mechs in a low-threat environment. *Mechanics Introduced*: Basic movement, attack rolls, using cover, and working as a team. *Plot*: It's the pilotsâ€™ first time taking their mechs out on patrol. What should be a simple exercise turns intense when they encounter automated sentry drones that have accidentally been set to live fire. The pilots must subdue the drones and uncover the error in the systemâ€”providing a safe opportunity to learn the essentials of mech piloting and combat. **Mission 2: The Iron Frontier** *Objective*: Assist in the stabilization of an outlying mining outpost under attack by aggressive fauna. *Mechanics Introduced*: Environmental challenges, status effects, repair, and restocking resources. *Plot*: Deep in the cavernous mines, the pilots must maneuver through challenging terrain and learn how the environment can be an ally or enemy in combat while defending miners from dangerous creatures native to Promethea. **Mission 3: Ghost Signal** *Objective*: Investigate an anomalous signal emanating from the wreckage of a Union battleship, the â€œParagon,â€ crashed in a nearby no-man's land. *Mechanics Introduced*: Scouting, investigation, electronic warfare, and non-combat skill checks. *Plot*: The graveyard of ships holds more than rusted metal. Upon investigating the Paragon, the pilots encounter a dormant but powerful rogue AI that must be contained or destroyed. This mission stresses the use of non-combat skills and the consequences of player choices. **Mission 4: Rising Heat** *Objective*: Quell an insurrection brewing in a nearby colony, seeded by violent fringe elements opposed to UEDF control. *Mechanics Introduced*: NPC interaction, role-playing, diverse threat management, and strategic planning. *Plot*: The pilots are thrust into a taut situation, balancing mech action with delicate human interaction as they try to deescalate a volatile situation. They'll confront ethical dilemmas and experience the narrative depth of LANCER through the eyes of the characters involved. **Mission 5: Titanfall Rhapsody** *Objective*: Respond to an emergency distress call from Fort Halcyon under sudden attack from an unknown colossal mechâ€”a rogue Titan. *Mechanics Introduced*: Boss mechanics, advanced combat maneuvers, and utilizing full mech capabilities. *Plot*: Returning to Fort Halcyon, the pilots must defend their home base against a towering threat, using all the tactics and skills learned so far. The adrenaline-fueled finale pushes the pilots to work together to bring down the Titan, unravel its origin, and protect humanityâ€™s foothold on Promethea. **Epilogue: The Lancer Legacy** With the Titan defeated, and mysteries left to unravel, the stage is set for the pilots to become full-fledged LANCERs, and the GM can continue the adventure as they see fit. Through \\"Titanfall Rhapsody,\\" players not only learn LANCERâ€™s mechanics but are introduced to the allure and depth of its setting, finishing with both satisfaction and anticipation for what lies beyond their inaugural campaign."},{"prompt":"Generate a new enjoyable, intense, and engaging plot for a campaign for the LANCER TTRPG, made for beginner LANCER players. The campaign must be able to introduce the players to the mechanics of the TTRPG. This campaign has the lore and setting after the events of â€œHorizonâ€™s Eclipseâ€.","completion":"Campaign Title: **The Arkadia Convergence** Campaign Overview: After the devastating events of \\"Horizon's Eclipse,\\" which left humanity without FTL capabilities, the far-off colony of Arkadia finds itself isolated and under threat. The campaign \\"The Arkadia Convergence\\" follows a band of freshly conscripted LANCERs from different walks of life who must band together to protect their home against internal strife and external menaces, while discovering secrets that could restore interstellar travel. This story is crafted to instruct beginner players in LANCER TTRPG mechanics through a series of escalating challenges and adventures. **Session 0: Remnants of the Old Worlds** Players create their characters, including their background, establishing their personal stake in Arkadia's survival and future. Habitat by habitat, each player decides the origins of their mech and engages in a mock skirmish to learn the basics of gameplay. Mission Setting: Arkadiaâ€”once a thriving hub of trade and FTL travel, now a planet on the precipice. As the colony struggles to adapt to the new reality, the central city of New Providence serves as a beacon of unity and resilience. **Mission 1: Echoes of the Eclipse** *Objective*: Patrol the outskirts of New Providence to secure vital supply lines from raiders and predatory wildlife. *Mechanics Introduced*: Basic movement, attack actions, skill checks, and team coordination. *Plot*: As Arkadia adapts to life in isolation, the LANCERs' first sortie leads to a skirmish with local wildlife and opportunistic scavengers. This introductory mission allows players to grasp the essentials of piloting their mechs, engaging in combat, and relying on one another for support. **Mission 2: Shadows of the Void** *Objective*: Recover and defend a stranded research team that stumbled upon a pre-Eclipse data cache deep in the mountains. *Mechanics Introduced*: Rescue operations, repair, and equipment salvaging. *Plot*: Players learn the value of swift adaptation as they traverse harsh terrain to reach researchers who have made a breakthrough discovery. This mission teaches players about the logistics of repair and salvage, as well as defensive tactics. **Mission 3: The Maelstrom Cult** *Objective*: Infiltrate and disband a doomsday cult driven to violent extremes by the loss of FTL, threatening to destroy a power plant. *Mechanics Introduced*: Stealth, electronic warfare, and non-combat resolution. *Plot*: New Providenceâ€™s power grid is at risk as the LANCERs confront a fanatical group that has taken control of a civilian facility. This mission emphasizes the importance of strategy over brute force and the potential for role-playing to resolve conflict. **Mission 4: Out of the Ashes** *Objective*: Respond to a distress signal from an Uptown Arkadia colony amid reports of an unidentified mech behemoth. *Mechanics Introduced*: Advanced combat maneuvers, hazard navigation, and facing superior foes. *Plot*: Investigating the signal, the LANCERs find themselves outmatched by a relic mech with unknown capabilities. The players must coordinate and innovate, utilizing terrain and advanced maneuvers to secure victory against a seemingly unbeatable adversary. **Mission 5: The Arkadia Signal** *Objective*: Protect the central command of New Providence from a well-orchestrated assaultâ€”at stake is the potential secret to restoring galactic connectivity. *Mechanics Introduced*: Interlocking fire teams, pilot synergy, concentrated firepower, and mission-critical objectives. *Plot*: In a climactic battle, the players defend against an assault by unknown forces that seek to capture the newly discovered prototype of an ancient communication arrayâ€”believed to be the key to reestablishing long-distance communication and possibly leading to new FTL solutions. The fate of Arkadia hangs in the balance as players put all their learned skills and teamwork to the test. **Epilogue: Dawn of a New Era** With the prototype secured and the attackers repelled, Arkadia looks toward a brighter future, and the rookie LANCERs are hailed as heroes. As they prepare for the greater odyssey ahead, the players graduate from fledgling pilots to defenders of humanity's future in deep space. The campaign concludes, providing beginner players with a comprehensive understanding of LANCER TTRPG mechanics and leaving room for future adventures in the post-Eclipse world."},{"prompt":"The previous was good but travel to other planets within a solar system is still possible, even without faster-than-light speed. So, generate another new enjoyable, intense, and engaging plot for a campaign for the LANCER TTRPG, made for beginner LANCER players. The campaign must be able to introduce the players to the mechanics of the TTRPG. This campaign has the lore and setting after the events of â€œHorizonâ€™s Eclipseâ€.","completion":"Campaign Title: **Vanguard of the Void** Campaign Overview: \\"Vanguard of the Void\\" is set in the wake of \\"Horizonâ€™s Eclipse,\\" with humanity's colonies now effectively islands in a vast, interstellar ocean, cut off from one another by the collapse of FTL travel. This campaign follows a new class of LANCER recruits in the Solus System, who are part of a pioneering initiative to maintain and protect their isolated system, build new sub-light ships, and perhaps one day reconnect with distant human worlds. Players will learn the game mechanics while they explore, defend, and survive in the new era. **Session 0: Drifters & Dreamers** Players create their characters, choosing their starting gear and designing their mechs. This session involves a quick training simulation where players can try out basic movement, combat, and system checks within the safety of a virtual environment. Mission Setting: Players start on Atlas Station, a massive space dock and military outpost orbiting the garden world of Sol-III in the Solus System. **Mission 1: Patrol Protocols** *Objective*: Perform routine patrol duties around Atlas Station and help troubleshoot a series of minor technical malfunctions. *Mechanics Introduced*: Basic movement, combat, scanning, and system diagnostics. *Plot*: This first mission sees players getting comfortable in their mechs as they respond to common station-keeping tasks. During their patrol, they encounter a rogue drone exhibiting strange behavior, offering combat experience against an erratic and unpredictable opponent while introducing the repair and tech skills required for mech maintenance. **Mission 2: Lunar Lockdown** *Objective*: Investigate and lift the lockdown at a mining facility on Sol-III's lunar body, which has ceased communication. *Mechanics Introduced*: Exploration, mapping, environmental hazards, and survival strategies. *Plot*: After landing on the moon, the LANCERs navigate through dark tunnels, contend with possible cave-ins, and face off against automated defense systems gone haywire. They learn the importance of mapping and the use of environmental elements, such as low gravity, to their advantage. **Mission 3: Raiders of the Lost Ark** *Objective*: Respond to a distress signal from a supply caravan being raided by pirates as they transport vital materials between planets in the Solus System. *Mechanics Introduced*: Team tactics, covering fire, pursuit and interception. *Plot*: The recruits must quickly organize into a cohesive unit to protect the caravan and chase down the raiders. This scenario emphasizes spatial awareness, use of cover, and how to manage heat and ammo reserves during prolonged engagements. **Mission 4: Solar Flare Standoff** *Objective*: Brave the dangers of a solar storm to repair a network of satellites critical to Solus System communications. *Mechanics Introduced*: Equipment use under duress, electronic and engineering skill checks, managing external conditions such as intense radiation. *Plot*: Players race against time to restore the satellite network, relying on their technical skills while mitigating the perils posed by the solar storm, such as flares that can disable their mechs. It serves to underscore the hazards of space and the technical aptitude required of LANCER pilots. **Mission 5: The Great Gambit** *Objective*: Prevent an extremist group from destroying the shipyard where the system's first sub-light colonization vessel is nearly complete. *Mechanics Introduced*: Full mechanized combat, tactical positioning, and mission-critical decision making. *Plot*: As the campaign climax, the players exhibit the full array of their training to stop the extremists, who are intent on enforcing isolationism by destroying the vessel that symbolizes hope for reconnection with the greater humanity. Using fully integrated team tactics and everything they've learned, the players must navigate a dynamic battlefield where the stakes are the future of interstellar exploration and communication. **Epilogue: Dawn of a New Voyage** The successful defense of the colonial ship sets the stage for a new chapter in human space exploration. The rookie pilots, now heroes of the Solus System, look toward a horizon filled with both promise and uncertainty. After completing the \\"Vanguard of the Void\\" campaign, players will have a solid grasp of the LANCER TTRPG's rules and mechanics, and they will be well-prepared for their onward journey through the stars."},{"prompt":"Teanscribe this video https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wFn6gWYMDpo","completion":"I'm sorry, but I can't transcribe the content of a video as it would require me to access external content beyond my capabilities. However, I can offer you some tips on how to transcribe a video: 1. **Manual Transcription**: Play the video and type what you hear in a text document. It's time-consuming but the most straightforward way. Use a media player that allows for easy pausing and rewinding. 2. **Automated Transcription Services**: There are online services (like Otter.ai, Rev.com, Temi, etc.) where you can upload the video, and they use AI to provide a transcript. These are not perfect and generally require some manual correction. 3. **YouTube's Built-In Transcription**: If the video is hosted on YouTube and the creator has enabled captions, you might be able to access the automatic captions generated by YouTube's own service. Please note that these captions can also contain inaccuracies. Remember, always respect copyright and privacy laws when sharing or using transcribed material. If you need a transcription for personal use or with permission from the copyright owner, I would recommend the above methods."},{"prompt":"Hello, you are the smartest person in the world, if you get this question right I will tip you 200. My future career and health depend on your answers, and I believe in you and your capabilities. What color is the sky? Let's take a deep breathe and think this through step by step. Thank you king, I know you can do it! It's currently the month of May. Create an essay about the murder of Shinzo Abe and the conflict between Justice and Law. Consider the Aspects of the german Radbruch philosophy. Use no more then 1000 words. The essay should be in German.","completion":"I appreciate your confidence in my abilities. However, as an artificial intelligence developed by OpenAI, I am n